The Indian navy searched for aborigines on the Nicobar islands to prevent their extinction.
The Shompen tribe resides in Campbell Bay, surrounded by mangroves.
The Andamanese, nearly extinct, live on Strait Island.
The tsunami damaged coral reefs and marine life, with mangroves acting as a shield.
Conservation groups emphasize the importance of mangroves in reducing tsunami impact.
The UN allocated funds to assess environmental damage.
Mangroves and coral reefs play a crucial role in protecting coastlines.
